					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163661" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;" >MrWrong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1495200086 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 May 2017 13:21</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2826330">
									

<p>While you have thankfully toned down on the unlikeability of the speaker,<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-650322-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-650322-1')">1</a></sup> the content is not that interesting.</p>
<p>With 2912, the horror of clown breeding is implied and subtle. Here, you essentially stated that which were implied in 2912 and added stuff like selective breeding. Perhaps it is suitable, but not groundbreaking.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-650322-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-650322-1')">1</a>. I guess this works better than using every bigoted trope out there.</div>
</div>

