				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="2788421"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1495461836 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 May 2017 14:03</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2829096">
									

<p>I have similar feelings on this, but I find some parts of it funny, and that saves it from a downvote.</p>
<p>The horror and mystery of 2912, as stated before, was how fucked up and weird it got, especially the 'child breaker' part of the article. This, on the other hand, just outright removes the horror by telling us. And while for some that works better, but for me, my mind wandered for what exactly they <em>did to these kids</em>, and that's why it worked.</p>
<p>Not to say that nothing worked here. Far from it, I thought some parts were funny, but not enough to upvote.</p>

							</div>

								
					
