			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2826452">
									

<p>The last line is comedy gold. Everything else feels like a caricature of a caricature of a caricature, so far removed from any sense of actual character that it feels like you're writing a parody of the group. Aside from that, 2912 also worked in part because it didn't show all its cards and played up the horror angle by having being subtle while still maintaining an &quot;in your face&quot; vibe with its whole deal. You play this for laughs, but it loses everything I liked about that article.</p>

